    <briefdescription>
<para>Spawn condition that limits spawning based on a maximum rate per second. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1MaxPerSecCondition" kindref="compound">MaxPerSecCondition</ref> provides rate-limited spawning by calculating a spawn budget based on elapsed time and a configured maximum spawn rate. This enables smooth, time-distributed spawning rather than bursts.</para>
<para>The spawn budget is calculated as: `maxRequestsPerSecond * deltaTime`.</para>
<para>Example usage: ```cpp // Allow up to 10 spawns per second auto condition = std::make_unique&lt;MaxPerSecCondition&gt;(10); spawnSystem.setCondition(std::move(condition)); ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1SpawnCondition" kindref="compound">SpawnCondition</ref> for the base interface </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1spawn_1_1logic_1_1TimerSpawnCondition" kindref="compound">TimerSpawnCondition</ref> for interval-based spawning </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
